55 Wizard - Quellious</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usorenhsolarflare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soren H Solarflare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/01 3:48:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing mob that SUMMONS!</span><hr size=1> When soloing a summoning mob you must go with doing the quickest amount of damage you possibly can in the smallest amount of time.<br>
<br>
Rains are pretty much totally out of the picture because you greatly risk the mob summoning you into the rain yourself.<br>
<br>
Summoning mobs are really a wizards greatest foe.(next to those damn things that resist even lure grr).<br>
<br>
However, a rooted mob will still summon, there is a couple seconds between summons, meaning, you can back out and have time to get a spell off if lucky.  If you do want to be able to check soloed mob off the list then yes os would be seemingly the best place.<br>
<br>
However, in DN, there is a trap that can set of swarming beetles, and also a trap for mini phase spiders.<br>
<br>
DOn't f with the phase spider ones, you will die.  Actually don't mess with any of them.<br>
<br>
However one of my friends set off a trap while we were heading down to serpent.  Luckily it only unleashed two.  I killed them both, and believe it or not, one of them summoned me.  But hehe its not worth it, because if you set off 12, you will die, and fast, cause I did it once while exploring chetari lair.<br>
<br>
